-- Germany's Costs Rise for Shared Meads Weapons System, Handelsblatt Reports
-- B y   J e r e m y   v a n   L o o n
-- 2010-09-28T05:10:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-28/germany-s-costs-rise-for-shared-meads-weapons-system-handelsblatt-reports.html
German Defense Minister Karl-
Theodor zu Guttenberg plans to spend more on a weapons system
jointly developed with the U.S. and Italy than has been approved
by parliament,  Handelsblatt  reported.  The Meads system will cost 250 million euros ($337 million)
more to develop than was originally approved by the German
parliament, the newspaper said, citing defense ministry
documents.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Jeremy van Loon  in Berlin at 
 jvanloon@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Reed Landberg at 
 landberg@bloomberg.net  